text.__SUMMARY__: Conasprella  fenzani is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails and their allies.These cone snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans, therefore live ones should be handled carefully or not at all.
text.Description: The size of the shell attains 47 mm.
text.Distribution: This species occurs in the Pacific Ocean off Panama.
